erbert S. Klein provide a synthetic overview of the growth of São Paulo from 1850 to 1950, analyzing statistical data on demographics, agriculture, finance, trade, and infrastructure. Quantitative analysis of primary sources, including almanacs, censuses, newspapers, state and ministerial-level government documents, and annual government reports offers granular insight into state building, federalism, the coffee economy, early industrialization, urbanization, and demographic shifts. Luna and Klein compare São Paulo's transformation to other regions from the same period, making this an essential reference for understanding the impact of early periods of economic growth.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 4aBrazil. 4aCoffee. 4aDemographic History. 4aEconomic History. 4aFinancial History. 4aFiscal History. 4aPublic Works. 4aRailroads. 4aState Formation. 4aSão Paulo. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 19th Century.2bisacsh1 aKlein, Herbert S., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311070368940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781503604124zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503604124423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503604124.jpg  a978-3-11-070368-9  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles